title: noche
author: noche
content: Hi all, after to do a factory reset via webgui i got all the ligths on and my antminer s3 not work.Any help?Thanks.All the best.

comments.author: noche
comments.body: When I disconnect the Ethernet cable, the red and green lights, on.

comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: Can you still able to access the unit through the WebGUI?If not you might need USB to UART to revive this unit. There is an old guide on the forum that you can follow check this link below- https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=775662.0

There is an old guide on the forum that you can follow check this link below- https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=775662.0No, I can't access to the webgui.How to connect to the pc, the usb to uart?Thanks.

comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: Quote from: noche on November 14, 2023, 11:49:16 AMNo, I can't access to the webgui.How to connect to the pc, the usb to uart?Thanks.I hope that you read the guide that I posted above according to it you need to look for RX, TX, and GND. Connect the USB to UART to these terminals and connect it to the PC it should be able to communicate with the PC.Ok, the image from the old guide does not show I think better check the archive if you want to check the image here below.- https://web.archive.org/web/20150520040616/https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=775662.0
